#Multiple Image Graphic - Squares
##Multiple Squares Example - Minimal Config
###This demonstrates a minimal invocation of the widget with multiple images

rhtmlPictographs::graphic(0.8,400,400,'{"percentage":0.8,"numImages":3,"text-overlay":"foo","variableImageUrl":"https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/kyle-public-numbers-assets/htmlwidgets/CroppedImage/blue_square_512.png"}')

##Multiple Squares Example - Scale image based on percentage
###This demonstrates the direction: scale property
###Given we still are using a single cell with multiple images we can only specify one percentage.
###If we wanted each image to have a specific percentage then we would use a table of multiple cells (each potentially having multiple images),
###not a single cell with multiple images

rhtmlPictographs::graphic(0.8,400,400,'{"percentage":0.8,"direction":"scale","numImages":3,"text-overlay":"foo","variableImageUrl":"https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/kyle-public-numbers-assets/htmlwidgets/CroppedImage/blue_square_512.png"}')

##Multiple Squares Example - Text Header and Footer
###This demonstrates the use of header and footer text
###Notice how the adition of the footer messes with the internal horizontal padding ?!

rhtmlPictographs::graphic(0.8,400,400,'{"percentage":0.8,"numImages":3,"variableImageUrl":"https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/kyle-public-numbers-assets/htmlwidgets/CroppedImage/blue_square_512.png","text-header":"Big header","text-footer":"Big footer"}')

##Multiple Squares Example - Set DebugBorder to see whats up
###This demonstrates the use of debugBorder for visual aid
###You can see the padding is correct but now the images are being centred to maintain their aspect ratio

rhtmlPictographs::graphic(0.8,400,400,'{"percentage":0.8,"numImages":3,"variableImageUrl":"https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/kyle-public-numbers-assets/htmlwidgets/CroppedImage/blue_square_512.png","text-header":"Big header","text-footer":"Big footer","debugBorder":"anything"}')

##Multiple Squares Example - Add 2x font-size to the height and everything is good
###This demonstrates that adding height to compensate for the header and footer gets everything back to normal

rhtmlPictographs::graphic(0.8,400,448,'{"percentage":0.8,"numImages":3,"variableImageUrl":"https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/kyle-public-numbers-assets/htmlwidgets/CroppedImage/blue_square_512.png","text-header":"Big header","text-footer":"Big footer","debugBorder":"anything"}')

