#Multiple Image Graphic - configure inner padding ratios
##Multiple Image Example - set the inner padding to match the image size
###A value of 0.5 sets the padding = the image size
###For more info, these two parameters sets the padding value of the call to .rangebands : https://github.com/mbostock/d3/wiki/Ordinal-Scales#ordinal_rangeBands

rhtmlPictographs::graphic(1,400,400,'{"percentage":1,"numImages":3,"variableImageUrl":"https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/kyle-public-numbers-assets/htmlwidgets/CroppedImage/blue_square_512.png","interColumnPadding":"0.5","interRowPadding":"0.5"}')

##Multiple Image Example - set the inner padding to 0
###A value of 0 removes all inner padding
###For more info, these two parameters sets the padding value of the call to .rangebands : https://github.com/mbostock/d3/wiki/Ordinal-Scales#ordinal_rangeBands

rhtmlPictographs::graphic(1,400,400,'{"percentage":1,"numImages":3,"variableImageUrl":"https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/kyle-public-numbers-assets/htmlwidgets/CroppedImage/blue_square_512.png","interColumnPadding":"0","interRowPadding":"0"}')

